      <head>d’Ora (Santiago)</head>
      <div>

        <p>Photographic agency in <ref cRef="entity-008467">Santiago</ref>, <ref
            cRef="entity-005845">Chile</ref>.</p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <p>d’Ora was a photographic agency in the center of Santiago, the photographers of which
          were Herren <ref cRef="entity-008487">Gerstner</ref> and Lange. On her stay in <ref
            cRef="entity-008467">Santiago</ref> in Summer 1936, <ref cRef="entity-000771">Jeanette
            Schenker</ref> made several visits to the agency between June 5 and August 3, during
          which Lange’s wife helped her to find a more suitable guesthouse, and <ref
            cRef="entity-008487">Herr Gerstner</ref> enabled her to contact the conductor <ref
            cRef="entity-008475">Theo Buchwald</ref>, and provided the (outdated) address and
          mailbox number of her brother <ref cRef="entity-000783">Viktor Schiff</ref>.</p>

        <p>There seems to have been no connection with the <ref cRef="entity-002809">Atelier
            d’Ora</ref> on Wipplingerstraße in Vienna.</p>
      </div>
